Cooper County was named in honour of the Merchant and Philanthropist Sir Daniel Cooper (1821-1902).
Cooper County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It contains the town of Barellan . The Murrumbidgee River is the southern boundary.
